stock, a quick change barrel system with conversion kits for .300 BLK and other calibers available. Unlike the ACR however, the XCR is not made of polymer but rather is made entirely of metal, including the very rugged and tough FAST stock.  The XCR has a monolithic rail system as the upper reciever and the forend/handguard are a continuous single piece.  I have owned this rifle since late Skeleton stock for the XCR and this second stock is also included.  Though the skeleton stock is lighter, I personally prefer the FAST stock, which I find to be superior to the various stocks that are available for the SCAR or ACR.  The FAST stock not only extends to one of six positions, but it also has an adjustable cheek riser.  The r rifle's trigger has also been upgraded with Robinson's 2-stage match trigger which provides a pull weight of 3.5 lbs with a 2 lb. first stage and a 1.5 lb. second stage.  Relative to the 5.5 lb. single stage stock trigger, this upgrade greatly improves accuracy and rate of fire.  The stock single stage trigger is also included.  Another upgrade that I've added is the compensator/muzzle brake, which mitigates muzzle rise.  Finally, the stock pistol title: For Sale:  Franchi Spas12.
postcontent: Up for sale is my Franchi Spas 12.  This is the real deal.  As seen on movies such as Jurassic Park and the Terminator.  If you are looking at this listing, chances are you are familiar with this shotgun.  If not, please do your research.  This is an early model Imported Spas12.  It has a folding metal stock along with the sought after Shepard's hook.  It has the factory ghost ring sights and has the extended 8 round magazine tube.  This Spas has the early style lever switch saftey, which was later recalled by Franchi.  Again, please do your research.   In short, I bought this shotgun several years ago from a retired police officer.  The gun has some surface rusting on one side from being stored in the truck of a squad car, as well as some scratches on the outside of the receiver from being clamped down.  I planned on sending the gun into a gunsmith to have the cosmetic blemishes fixed as well as have it checked over.  The shotgun is 30 years old and I wanted to make sure it was checked before firing, and I would advise anyone interested to do the same.   The previous owner said the shotgun operated fine, and it seems to be mechanically sound.I have checked to see if the receiver shock absorber was in place, and it is.  So no worries there.   If you do your research, you will see this is a problem area.  Also, it seems to operate correctly, and the gun does switch from pump action to semi auto as it should.  I'm selling because my priorities have changed, and I hate letting it sit in the case.  It's time to let it go and let someone else enjoy it. The shotgun comes with a hard carry case.  Price is absolutely firm at $750.  You can't touch one of these for under $1200 these days.  I won't accept a penny less.  Please, serious buyers only.  No trades!   I will send photos to anyone interested.   I will do meets at Jays Sporting Goods in Clare Michigan only.  Zip code is 48617.
